~ deception_succeed
Alan: Fine, we need all the help we can get to stop the spread.[#sprite=04]
if Global.werewolf == Global.Character.ALAN
	Alan: The human form’s personality is completely overridden by the werewolf’s aggression. [#sprite=02]
else
	Alan: From what we’ve observed, it seems like the human form’s personality is completely overridden by the werewolf’s aggression.[#sprite=02]
Protag: Interesting… so even if the human is completely harmless, then the werewolf form will still attack others?[#sprite=05]
if Global.werewolf == Global.Character.ALAN
	Alan: Indeed. They also experience immense pain while transforming. Many werewolves I know have needed painkillers just to survive the transformation. [#sprite=01]
else
	Alan: Indeed. More interestingly, they experience immense pain while transforming. Most werewolves I’ve dealt with have needed painkillers just to survive the transformation.[#sprite=01]
Protag: [i] Interesting… What a horrible disease… [/i] [#sprite=04]
Protag: Do they remember anything from their time as a werewolf?[#sprite=01]
if Global.werewolf == Global.Character.ALAN
	Alan: Nothing except for fuzzy memories.[#sprite=03]
else
	Alan: Nothing except for fuzzy memories, from what we’ve observed.[#sprite=03]
Protag: So they could go around killing on full moons and not even remember it?[#sprite=17]
Alan: Indeed. Many people with Lycanthropy don’t even realize they do until someone else tells them. They feel extreme agony, yes, but their brains usually suppress the memory without an explanation for the pain.[#sprite=04]
Protag: What about any physical signs?[#sprite=05]
Alan: None. Except on full moons, werewolves are completely indistinguishable from normal people.[#sprite=01]
Protag: Interesting, thank you for your cooperation in this interrogation. I’ll see you again later.[#sprite=01]
=> end_dialogue

~ deception_fail
Alan: Do you think I’m stupid? You didn’t know werewolves existed 10 minutes ago, there’s no way you actually care about this.[#sprite=04]
Alan: Lying isn’t going to make me any more willing to cooperate with you.[#sprite=01]
Protag: I’m not lying! I really do want to help.[#sprite=17]
Alan: Nice try. It’s not going to work though.[#sprite=02]
Protag: [i] It’s not even really a lie. Sure, I want to solve the case first and foremost, but I also want to help. I guess Alan didn’t buy it, though.[/i] [#sprite=16]
=> end_dialogue

~ intimidation_succeed
Alan: Ugh, fine, I’ll tell you. I’m not a werewolf, for the record, and I don’t appreciate you implying I could be.[#sprite=04]
Protag: Just tell me what you know about werewolves.[#sprite=01]
Alan: Even if I was a werewolf, you wouldn’t be able to tell by looking at me. Werewolves are indistinguishable from humans when it’s not the full moon. The only way to know for sure is to watch someone transform, which comes with obvious risks.[#sprite=03]
if Global.werewolf == Global.Character.ALAN
	Alan: Lycanthropy completely overrides the person’s human personality and just replaces it with pure rage and aggression. There’s no such thing as a tame werewolf. They’re all… mindless beasts. [#sprite=05]
else
	Alan: Lycanthropy seems to completely override the person’s human personality and just replace it with pure rage and aggression. As a result, there’s no such thing as a tame werewolf.[#sprite=05]
Protag: That’s interesting… So does that mean werewolves ruthlessly kill and turn, but the person doesn’t even mean to?[#sprite=05]
if Global.werewolf == Global.Character.ALAN
	Alan: I doubt werewolves would do much turning if they were of sound mind. They don’t even remember what happened while they were transformed. [#sprite=01]
else
	Alan: I still don’t understand why people don’t just trap themself in a box or something to preclude the killings.[#sprite=01]
Protag: [i] Pity they don’t, my job would be much easier if they did… [/i] [#sprite=04]
Protag: If that’s all, thank you for the information. Sorry for, uh, accusing you of being a werewolf.[#sprite=01]
if Global.werewolf == Global.Character.ALAN
	Alan: ...Whatever. [#sprite=02]
else
	Alan: Technically, I could still be one. The culprit was clearly a werewolf, after all, and I’m one of the suspects.[#sprite=02]
	Protag: …I’ll keep that in mind.[#sprite=04]
=> end_dialogue

